  "text": "Human myeloid and erythroid cells have also been induced in mice. When stromal cells secreting human EPO and IL-3 were cotransplanted into bone marrow with CD34 1 human HSCs in beige/nude/ XID mice, detectable levels of human red blood cells were transiently produced with an increase in hematocrit from 40% to 80%. [CITATION_1] A recent publication also confirmed that EPO and IL-3 treatment could further improve the peripheral human red blood cells (RBCs) levels in humanized NOD/SCID and NOD/SCID/cc 2/2 mice. [CITATION_2] These results show that GM-CSF, M-CSF and IL-3 are critical for human myeloid cell development in mice due to their high species-specific activities, but EPO shows crossreactivity as mouse red blood cells also expand.",
